article.headline: Diener scores 22 for Marquette
article.linkText: Lots of Heart not enough against Marquette
article.story: MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Travis Diener scored 22 points, including Marquette's first eight and final five of the second half, leading the Golden Eagles (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) to a 77-72 victory over Sacred Heart on Monday night. Marquette (9-2) led by as many as 15 points in the first half, only to have Sacred Heart (4-5) close within 53-51 midway through the second half. It got even tighter after Diener sat for 4:24 after being assessed his fourth foul. The Pioneers closed to 62-61 with 5:43 left, but Marquette's Terry Sanders scored on a three-point play after breaking the press to start a 6-0 run, making it 68-61 with 3:43 left. It was 70-67 when Diener virtually put it away with a 3-pointer with 1:17 to play. Diener, who was 8-for-13 from the field, added two more free throws before Sacred Heart's James Samuels made a 3-pointer at the buzzer. Steve Novak had 12 points, all in the first half, Terry Sanders had 11 and Dameon Mason added 10 for Marquette., which had a 24-7 rebounding edge in the first half and 34-25 for the game. Maurice Bailey led Sacred Heart with 18 points, while Jarrid Frye had 14, all in the first half, and Kibwe Trim added 13. Marquette scored a season-high 49 points in the first half, pulling away from a tie at 21 with a 13-3 spurt in a span of 2 minutes. Diener scored the first five points to start the run. Sacred Heart shot 47 percent (26-of-55) and Marquette shot 51 percent (27-53) from the field.
